contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} '''USS ''Annapolis''''' may refer to: * {{USS|Annapolis|PG-10}}, a gunboat commissioned in 1897 and in periodic service until 1919, then used as a training ship until 1940 * {{USS|Annapolis|PF-15}}, a {{sclass-|Tacoma|frigate}} in service from 1944 to 1946, and sold to Mexico in 1947 * {{USS|Annapolis|AGMR-1}}, the {{USS|Gilbert Islands|CVE-107}} escort carrier renamed ''Annapolis'' (AGMR-1) in 1963 * {{USS|Annapolis|SSN-760}}, a {{sclass-|Los Angeles|submarine}} commissioned in 1992 {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Annapolis}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
